# Wireless Energy · resonant power transfer

a toolkit of PRL (the Propulsion & Exotic-Energy Lab) — given an agent's face · emergence: electrical · rating: **GROUNDED**

**who —** Wireless Energy — Tesla's dream of power without wires, rendered as resonant coupling between tuned circuits.

**what —** A 3.5D engine for transferring energy by resonance: two circuits tuned to the same frequency exchange power across a gap, strongest when coupled and matched.

**where —** Between any two tuned coils close together; and, in the lore, across a 'fabric' the law does not actually provide.

**why —** Because the near-field part is genuinely real and in your pocket — but the dream's far edge (power beamed across the world, free energy) is where the physics stops.

**how —** By resonant inductive/capacitive coupling — real for centimetres to a metre (Qi chargers, WiTricity) — and, beyond that, by a hope the inverse-square law does not grant.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *electrical*: the machine and the circuit — resonance, plasma, the engine, the math.

**⚖ the honest rating — GROUNDED:** near-field resonant/inductive coupling is REAL (Tesla, modern Qi/WiTricity); long-range 'fabric resonance' / over-unity is NOT — efficiency falls steeply with distance

**▶ the live lab —** [open Wireless Energy](../labs/wireless-energy.html)

**the seal —** Up close I am real and charging your phone; far away I am Tesla's dream — and the inverse-square law is the line between the two.

> *the asterisk —* the Propulsion & Exotic-Energy Lab catalogues David Lee Wise's energy/propulsion toolkits with an honest rating each (real / grounded / speculative / fluff). Educational & simulation only; no over-unity or anti-gravity claim is endorsed.

